India’s Foreign Reserves Fall $1.2 Billion to $311.5 Billion

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-10-07T11:33:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/india-s-foreign-reserves-fall-1-2-billion-to-311-5-billion.html
India’s foreign-exchange reserves
fell $1.2 billion to $311.5 billion in the week ended Sept. 30,
the Mumbai-based  Reserve Bank  of India said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Foreign-currency assets declined $1.23 billion to $275.7
billion, while the nation’s gold reserves increased by $348
million to $28.7 billion, the central bank said.  India’s special drawing rights with the International
Monetary Fund increased $7 million to $4.5 billion while its
reserves with the IMF contracted $345 million to $2.6 billion.  Total reserves climbed by $17.3 billion in the past year,
the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tushar Dhara in  New Delhi  at 
